                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>\n                                        <date>9<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> March 1849</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>Reverend Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">In the article “The Union of Israelites”\n                                        in=<lb/>=serted in the occident for\n                                                  <date><sic>march</sic></date>, just reached me, I\n                                        observe<lb/> a material change has taken place in\n                                                  <persName>Dr. Wise's</persName> original plan<lb/>\n                                        for heading a meeting <add>?</add> “That it shall consist of\n                                        none but<lb/> delegates to be elected by any Jewish\n                                        congregation in the United States”</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I perceive likewise that unless 20 congregations\n                                        respond to<lb/> the requisition the meeting will not take\n                                        place—Permit me<lb/> a few remarks on both points. 1. I\n                                        think it will be better to<lb/> afford Individuals, likewise\n                                        not delegated by any congregation, the<lb/> opportunity to\n                                        attend the meeting on signifying their intention to do\n                                        so.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I will give my reasons for this. As every member\n                                        of the Jewish<lb/> community is deeply interested in the\n                                        question of a Union, all and<lb/> every one ought to have\n                                        the faculty to attend such a meeting there<lb/> to consider\n                                        and decide whether a union be necessary. It<lb/> may then be\n                                        understood that 20 accessions to the requisition,<lb/>\n                                        whether of delegates or private individuals, shall be\n                                        deemed<lb/> the sufficient number, for holding the meeting,\n                                        not however<lb/> limiting it to that number if more should\n                                        have notified their<lb/> intention to attend it. 2. If the\n                                        assembly is to be constituted<lb/> of delegates only from\n                                        the congregations it may consist of many<lb/> if not of a\n                                        majority of individuals knowing little of the matters to\n                                        be<lb/> discussed, because appointed by congregations who at\n                                        this stage<lb/> may be equally uninformed upon them. In\n                                        fact, at the present</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3dz03j37/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
