                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3dz03j37/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>in the history of your nation, and in the history of the world\n                                        constitute a<lb/> series of events and circumstances\n                                        connected with its operations—</p>\n                              <p>It was my intention to have brought the whole subject down to\n                                        the<lb/> present period but found it would trail to a much\n                                        greater<lb/> length than at first contemplated. I may\n                                        however resume<lb/> the subject hereafter for the occident\n                                        or its reverend editor's<lb/> signifying his wish to have it\n                                        to his <add>?</add> Adwriter—</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(10)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">A A. Lindo</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>In my letter 2 in the occident for <date>March</date> a very\n                                        material omission<lb/> of the word “<hi rend=\"underline\"\n                                                  >but</hi>” has occurred. In the 1<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                                                  >st</hi> ,, the principles to<lb/> constitute the\n                                                  bares<add>?</add> of a Union, advertising to “the\n                                        effects of deviat<add>?</add><lb/> from our received\n                                        religious institutions &amp;c” The compositor says<lb/>\n                                        “whilst it cannot be productive of prejudicial effects to\n                                        themselves<lb/> &amp;c”—whereas I said, and I think you will\n                                        find it so in the<lb/> copy sent you. “Whilst it cannot <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">but</hi> be productive of<lb/>\n                                        prejudicial effects to themselves” &amp;c. Have the\n                                        goodness, by an<lb/> arterial reference, aside Letter 3 to a\n                                        note at bottom of page<lb/> to correct this\n                                                  mistake—<persName role=\"author\">AAL</persName></p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Reverend Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3dz03j37/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
